node.text:
So stoked for Surfer Blood tomorrow night! Saturday August 21st! 
This will be a super fun night and just what we all need right now. 🪅🎸🎶🎤🎹👩🏻‍🎤👨🏼‍🎤

Come rock out and let off some steam!
🕺🏻 💃🏼♨️THREE bands for a full night of music under the stars!
4 packs available with special pricing. So gather friends, family, or the neighbors and come let loose at Pappy’s. 
Doors at 6 pm

*In order to have the safest show environment and tour possible, Surfer Blood requires proof of vaccination or a negative COVID-19 test within 72 hours a requirement for entry to all of their shows.

node.text:
Hi y'all,

Waxahatchee has announced that all of her shows will be vaccine only. All the purchasers will be made aware of this as well. If anybody is requesting refunds please direct them to this email: help@dice.fm

We look forward to a great show! See you guys next month. Please scroll through pics and you can read @waxa_katie personal statement. 

From the artist and management:

Let’s return to live music safely. For the Waxahatchee show on 9/25/21 we will enforce the requirements of each venue, which currently requires that guests be fully vaccinated for Covid-19. 

All attendees must provide proof of COVID Vaccination via a CDC-approved physical vaccination card or digitally via  https://myvaccinerecord.cdph.ca.gov/ with QR code presented at the door. 

In addition, masks will be required unless actively eating or drinking. These are the guidelines we must follow to ensure that we do our part in keeping our community safe.

#pappyandharriets #pioneertown #staysafe #livemusic #americana #womeninmusic

Summer Sundays are for grilling! 🍔🥩🍖
 
Temps have cooled just slightly…and the days and nights are 💯perfection. 
We’ve opened up more outdoor seating again so people can feel comfortable if they don’t want to eat inside. And nature has complied with the most stunning nights since May. 

See you at the Palace for ribs, burgers, 🍻 beers Mac n’ cheese and cocktails! 🍹🌠

node.text:
Hey Fans:
Some bummer news from Bachelor:

"Due to unforeseen circumstances, Bachelor will no longer be hitting the road for the following shows. However, Ellen will still be supporting Lucy Dacus as Palehound on the first leg of her tour. Tickets for our headline shows will be refunded at point of purchase. Please get vaccinated and stay safe."

Unfortunately we may see a lot more of this in coming months. Pappy's is trying to stay safe and deal with a constantly shifting landscape, with not much help or guidance. It's what everyone in the music and restaurant industries are dealing with. So please be kind and remember we're all in this together, want to keep the restaurant going, and the music flowing!

This poster was created by local Pioneertown artist @rexatron5000 
We loved em’ so much we did a limited run. But you can get one FREE with purchase of two tickets to Surfer Blood Saturday August 21st! 🦈🏄‍♀️🏄🏼🏄🏽‍♂️

We’re moving this to our outdoor stage for a safer experience. This will be a really great night of music under the stars with 3 bands!
Doors at 6 pm to give us time to get everyone checked in. 🦈

Please bring negative Covid test within 72 hours or your fully vaxxed card or digital record. 
Find it here: 
https://myvaccinerecord.cdph.ca.gov/

Support from Worn Tin @floppydiskbuttbaby and Wake Up Band @wakeupband

node.text:
We are postponing our beloved Sunday Band and open mic until further notice. Negative tests and vaccines are required for large outdoor shows with major artists as per requirements for 900+ people packed together. 

We’d love to be able to do it all. But we are trying to stay safe, and also be practical. 

You don’t need a negative test or vaccine to dine. So come have the best bbq and comfort food this side of the Mississippi! 

Cold beer, tangy cocktails, ribs, Mac n’ cheese, nachos, catfish sandwiches and great company are always on tap!

node.text:
🚨FOR ALL UPCOMING OUTDOOR SHOWS🚨

THIS DOES NOT APPLY TO DINING

In the interest of keeping our guests and staff protected and healthy, Alex G and Pappy + Harriet’s will now require all attendees of Alex G’s upcoming show on Saturday August 7th to show proof of either a full COVID-19 vaccination or negative COVID-19 PCR test result.
🚨THIS APPLIES TO ALL SHOWS GOING FORWARD🚨
Refunds applies to shows that are, "Presented by Pappy + Harriets." 
Contact Hello@pappyandharriets.com

PLEASE CHECK YOUR TICKETS CAREFULLY AND CONTACT OUTSIDE PROMOTERS WHO YOU BOUGHT TICKETS THROUGH FOR REFUNDS
 
You can find your record here:
https://myvaccinerecord.cdph.ca.gov

All attendees will be required to show one of the following for entry at Pappy + Harriet’s on August 7th along with a government issued ID:

•	Your vaccine card
•	A clear and legible photocopy of your vaccine card
•	Photo of your vaccine card on your phone
•	A digital vaccine passport or record
•	A negative COVID-19 PCR test result obtained within 72 hours of the event
 
In addition, we are asking all patrons to do the following while on site: Comply with the Pappy + Harriet’s Fan Health Pledge and wear a mask whenever indoors.
 
If you purchased a ticket and are not vaccinated and cannot get tested, we will happily refund your money. Please e-mail hello@pappyandharriets.com with your confirmation number and we will immediately issue a refund.
 
Any other questions should be directed to hello@pappyandharriets.com

node.text:
Foo Fighters Approved Rock!

This wickedly fun band is opening for the Foo Fighters in November and Pappy’s gets them fresh off that that Mexico City date! The LA times compared the compelling lead singer to, “moving like a wick on a smoking firecracker.” 
The music ranges from melancholy ’80s post-punk to ’90s grunge Intense, but with a veil of dreaminess. 
Support: Gustaf
and Bad Waitress

Show: Friday, December 3rd, 2021
Tickets on sale: Friday, August 6th at 10am LOCAL

@killsbirdsmusic @badwaitressband @gustaf_nyc
